2. Use consistent indentation (e.g. 4 spaces) for readability.
6. Use consistent naming conventions (e.g. capitalize defined terms like "Work", "Source", etc.)
8. Verify all terms are defined before use (e.g. "Work" is used before it is defined).
9. Check for unused or undefined terms/variables.
This covers some of the common code quality best practices. Let me know if you need any clarification or have additional questions!